Huntsman Reports Assets of as Much as $71 Million in Disclosure

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   D .   S a l a n t
-- 
2011-09-09T23:03:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-09/huntsman-reports-assets-of-as-much-as-71-million-in-disclosure.html
Former Utah Governor  Jon Huntsman 
owns assets of between $16 million and $71 million, according to
his personal financial disclosure form released today.  Huntsman, 51, reported ownership of between $5 million and
$25 million in his family’s holding company, which owns stock in
Huntsman Corp., a Salt Lake City-based chemical company. His
assets also include a rental apartment in Coronado, California,
valued at between $1 million and $5 million.  He reported a bank installment loan valued at between $1
million and $5 million that was scheduled to be repaid last
month, and credit card debt valued at between $100,000 and
$250,000.  Huntsman served as ambassador to China during President
Barack Obama’s administration before returning to the U.S. to
seek the Republican presidential nomination.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan D. Salant in  Washington  at 
 jsalant@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Mark Silva  at   msilva34@bloomberg.net . 